    <!-- Detailed Remedies -->
    <string name="remedy_white_spot_detail">
        White Spot Disease (Ich) is a common parasite.\n\n
        <b>Remedy Steps:</b>\n
        1. Slowly raise water temperature to 28-30°C.\n
        2. Add 2-3 grams of non-iodized salt per liter of water.\n
        3. Use anti-parasite medications like Malachite Green or Formalin (follow package instructions).\n
        4. Perform partial water changes regularly.
    </string>
    <string name="remedy_fin_rot_detail">
        Fin Rot is a bacterial infection, often caused by poor water quality or stress.\n\n
        <b>Remedy Steps:</b>\n
        1. Immediately perform a 25-50% water change.\n
        2. Check and clean your water filter.\n
        3. Use a broad-spectrum antibiotic medication available at aquaculture supply stores.\n
        4. Ensure fish are not overcrowded.
    </string>
    <string name="remedy_healthy">No specific remedy needed. The fish appears to be healthy. Continue monitoring.</string>

